WEBVTT

00:24.150 --> 00:27.528
JEAN: Eddie and Jean met
and fell in love.

00:29.488 --> 00:33.325
Eddie and Jean got married
and bought a house.

00:34.452 --> 00:37.204
Eddie and Jean
were gonna have a kid

00:37.288 --> 00:39.498
but didn’t.

00:39.582 --> 00:43.502
So, every morning,
Eddie kisses Jean,

00:43.586 --> 00:46.505
Eddie leaves the house,

00:46.589 --> 00:49.091
and Jean’s alone.

00:49.175 --> 00:52.178
("I Wouldn’t Be Surprised"
by Bobbie Gentry playing)

01:02.396 --> 01:06.859
♪ If the ground were to freeze ♪

01:06.942 --> 01:11.197
♪ Underneath my feet ♪

01:11.280 --> 01:15.075
♪ In the summertime ♪

01:15.159 --> 01:21.999
♪ I wouldn’t be surprised ♪

01:23.167 --> 01:27.922
♪ If the rain from the skies ♪

01:28.005 --> 01:32.051
♪ Should put out my eyes ♪

01:32.134 --> 01:35.471
♪ And make me blind ♪

01:35.554 --> 01:42.144
♪ I wouldn’t be surprised ♪

01:43.437 --> 01:46.774
♪ ’Cause nothing surprises me ♪

01:46.857 --> 01:49.819
♪ Ever since you said to me ♪

01:49.902 --> 01:56.408
(over speakers):
♪ "Goodbye..." ♪

01:56.492 --> 01:58.494
(song continues faintly
in distance)

02:34.655 --> 02:36.407
Fucking Eddie, come on.

02:36.490 --> 02:39.076
♪ Ever since you said to me ♪

02:39.159 --> 02:42.496
-♪ "Goodbye..." ♪
-(door opens)

02:42.580 --> 02:45.124
Eddie, have you seen
the scissors? I...

02:45.207 --> 02:46.750
(panting)

02:50.212 --> 02:52.590
You’re wearing it.
Looks real good on you.

02:52.673 --> 02:55.593
♪ Then she took you
away from me ♪

02:55.676 --> 02:57.261
♪ So suddenly... ♪

02:57.344 --> 02:58.679
(puts knife on counter)

02:58.762 --> 03:00.389
Who’s that?

03:03.350 --> 03:04.977
He’s our baby.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.981
There were still some tags.

03:12.026 --> 03:14.028
Aren’t you gonna say something?

03:14.111 --> 03:16.447
♪ I wouldn’t be surprised... ♪

03:16.530 --> 03:18.032
This some kind of
sick joke, Eddie?

03:18.115 --> 03:19.658
’Cause I’m not really
in the mood.

03:19.742 --> 03:20.868
-No.
-(music stops)

03:20.951 --> 03:22.244
(door closes)

03:23.662 --> 03:25.581
It’s a baby, Jean.

03:25.664 --> 03:27.875
I can see that.

03:27.958 --> 03:30.336
It’s all worked out.

03:30.419 --> 03:32.421
He’s our baby.

03:46.060 --> 03:48.062
-(baby fussing)
-(Eddie talking quietly)

04:16.966 --> 04:18.509
Come here, look.

04:18.592 --> 04:20.594
(fussing continues)

04:21.720 --> 04:23.138
(Eddie clicks tongue)

04:24.348 --> 04:25.975
Here, you can...

04:27.977 --> 04:29.603
Where did you...?

04:31.188 --> 04:33.190
Uh, not now, Jean.

04:38.737 --> 04:40.698
(Eddie sighs)

04:40.781 --> 04:42.741
It’s your baby.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.956
What’s his name?

04:49.039 --> 04:50.666
That’s up to you.

04:55.295 --> 04:57.214
(phone ringing)

04:57.297 --> 04:59.299
(fussing continues)

05:19.445 --> 05:21.447
(phone continues ringing)

05:22.656 --> 05:24.658
♪ ♪

05:26.827 --> 05:29.163
-(phone clicks)
-EDDIE: Yeah?

05:29.246 --> 05:31.373
(Eddie continues
talking faintly)

05:31.457 --> 05:33.459
(fussing quiets)

05:51.226 --> 05:53.228
(kids chattering playfully)

06:03.030 --> 06:05.032
-(playful chatter continues)
-(birds chirping)

06:13.248 --> 06:15.250
(baby cooing)

06:24.968 --> 06:26.929
(man speaking quietly
over radio)

06:28.138 --> 06:29.431
(egg thumping on pan)

06:30.307 --> 06:31.600
(sizzling)

06:31.683 --> 06:33.018
-(baby crying)
-(Jean gasps)

06:35.687 --> 06:37.564
Something burning?

06:37.648 --> 06:39.399
-Yes.
-(baby fussing)

06:40.692 --> 06:42.694
(lawn mower buzzing in distance)

06:52.913 --> 06:54.581
Where’s the other egg?

06:54.665 --> 06:56.250
On the floor.

06:56.333 --> 06:58.502
(laughing)

06:58.585 --> 07:00.587
(toast crunching)

07:02.172 --> 07:03.298
Mmm.

07:03.382 --> 07:04.550
(doorbell rings)

07:04.633 --> 07:06.635
I’ll get it.
I’ll get it.

07:09.138 --> 07:10.347
(sighs)

07:10.430 --> 07:12.349
Hey, I’m not
gonna be home tonight.

07:12.432 --> 07:13.851
You’ll be all right?

07:15.978 --> 07:17.980
(grunts)
That’s my little firecracker.

07:20.065 --> 07:22.192
Eddie, I...

07:27.865 --> 07:29.449
What?

07:30.534 --> 07:32.870
(doorbell rings)

07:32.953 --> 07:34.371
Nothing.

07:38.417 --> 07:40.043
Hey.

07:42.045 --> 07:44.840
Don’t worry about it so much.

07:44.923 --> 07:47.050
(whispers):
Your eggs are terrible anyway.

07:50.554 --> 07:51.680
(door opens)

07:51.763 --> 07:53.891
Hey, Singh. Come on in.

07:53.974 --> 07:55.100
Nice to see you.

07:55.184 --> 07:56.935
Rowe, thanks for being here.

07:57.019 --> 07:58.187
Oh.

07:58.270 --> 07:59.938
-Come on, come on.
-(grunting)

08:00.022 --> 08:01.648
-My boy.
-I’m so fucking
enjoying it here.

08:01.732 --> 08:03.233
Hey, hey, watch your mouth.
I got a kid.

08:03.317 --> 08:05.652
All right, all right.
I know.

08:05.736 --> 08:07.362
Hold on one second.

08:12.159 --> 08:14.161
(baby crying)

08:18.290 --> 08:20.292
(crickets chirping)

08:22.419 --> 08:24.421
(phone ringing)

08:28.133 --> 08:30.135
(phone continues ringing)

08:35.933 --> 08:37.142
(grunts softly)

08:43.023 --> 08:44.650
(ringing stops)

08:57.871 --> 08:59.790
-(loud pounding on door)
-(gasps)

08:59.873 --> 09:02.209
(panting)

09:02.292 --> 09:04.002
(loud pounding on door
continues)

09:14.429 --> 09:15.847
Jimmy.

09:17.849 --> 09:19.309
You’re okay?

09:19.393 --> 09:20.602
Yeah. Why?

09:23.105 --> 09:25.399
-(lock clicks)
-What are you doing?

09:25.482 --> 09:26.900
No one’s here?

09:29.945 --> 09:31.363
What are you talking about?

09:31.446 --> 09:33.740
Something happened tonight.
We have to go.

09:33.824 --> 09:35.575
Now, Jean.

09:35.659 --> 09:37.286
♪ ♪

09:37.369 --> 09:39.204
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on. Let’s go.

09:39.288 --> 09:40.414
Jimmy, what are you doing here?

09:40.497 --> 09:42.165
Go ahead, down the hall.

09:43.208 --> 09:45.794
Why are you in Eddie’s closet?

09:45.877 --> 09:47.462
You don’t have time to pack.

09:47.546 --> 09:49.881
-You can get stuff on the way.
-You got to slow down.

09:49.965 --> 09:52.217
I-I don’t know what’s happening.

09:52.301 --> 09:54.845
You’ll work out with Cal
where you’re gonna go.

09:54.928 --> 09:57.306
Who the hell is Cal?
Where is Eddie?

09:57.389 --> 10:00.017
This is 200 grand.

10:00.100 --> 10:02.686
Cal will manage how the money
is spent, but you hold onto it.

10:02.769 --> 10:05.022
-Is Eddie okay?
-You give him ten grand
right away,

10:05.105 --> 10:07.024
and you can work it out from
there if he stays with you.

10:07.107 --> 10:09.192
Who told you to tell me
all of this?

10:09.276 --> 10:10.861
What...

10:10.944 --> 10:12.029
Jimmy.

10:12.112 --> 10:14.156
Jimmy, Jimmy, hey, hey.
Stop, stop, stop.

10:14.239 --> 10:17.326
Jimmy, it’s me. It’s Jean.

10:17.409 --> 10:20.203
Please tell me what’s happening.

10:20.287 --> 10:22.289
Just take the bag, sweetheart.

10:26.001 --> 10:27.919
Go wake up the kid.

10:28.003 --> 10:30.005
♪ ♪

10:35.510 --> 10:37.512
(baby crying)

10:42.351 --> 10:44.353
♪ ♪

11:09.503 --> 11:10.921
I’m Cal.

11:12.297 --> 11:14.299
(baby fussing)

11:22.307 --> 11:24.309
(engine starts)

11:31.191 --> 11:33.193
(brakes squeak softly)

11:48.542 --> 11:50.585
JEAN: All Eddie said is
he wouldn’t be home tonight,

11:50.669 --> 11:52.921
but he says that all the time,
and then I wake up

11:53.004 --> 11:55.799
in the middle of the night and
he’s right there next to me.

11:55.882 --> 11:57.342
-(baby crying)
-I don’t know what’s going on

11:57.426 --> 12:00.804
or who you are or why
any of this is happening.

12:00.887 --> 12:02.139
(crying continues)

12:02.222 --> 12:04.099
He’s never like this.

12:04.182 --> 12:07.102
It’s like he knows
something isn’t right.

12:07.185 --> 12:11.064
I mean, he cries when
he’s hungry, but he just ate.

12:12.357 --> 12:14.484
Don’t they say that
about babies?

12:14.568 --> 12:17.487
They can feel an energy, like...

12:17.571 --> 12:19.114
like, even if
you’re trying to hide it,

12:19.197 --> 12:21.116
they know how you really feel.

12:21.199 --> 12:22.492
(crying continues)

12:23.535 --> 12:25.537
(shushing softly)

12:29.541 --> 12:31.543
(baby fussing quietly)

12:34.171 --> 12:36.423
You have your own?

12:39.968 --> 12:41.386
No.

12:47.809 --> 12:49.811
(water running)

12:52.814 --> 12:55.192
(traffic passing outside)

12:55.275 --> 12:57.277
(knob creaks, water stops)

13:03.909 --> 13:05.327
(coos softly)

13:07.329 --> 13:08.955
(door opens)

13:18.715 --> 13:20.634
I get kicked out of my house
in the middle of the night,

13:20.717 --> 13:22.344
and we’re sent with you,
a complete stranger...

13:22.427 --> 13:24.471
-You know what Eddie is, right?
-That he’s a thief?

13:24.554 --> 13:26.223
-That he steals for a living?
-Jean.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.725
-Yes, I know what Eddie is.
-Then you know what’s going on.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.602
Look, I don’t know who you are,
but I don’t like the way

13:30.685 --> 13:33.480
-you’re talking...
-I’m how you and
the baby stay safe.

13:34.523 --> 13:36.566
(call bell dings)

13:36.650 --> 13:37.776
Harry.

13:37.859 --> 13:39.361
Sorry?

13:39.444 --> 13:41.238
The baby.

13:41.321 --> 13:42.322
You said "the baby."

13:42.405 --> 13:43.865
I thought you might like
to know his name.

13:45.909 --> 13:47.536
(call bell dinging)

13:48.578 --> 13:49.913
Is he okay?

13:49.996 --> 13:51.456
(Harry fussing)

13:51.540 --> 13:53.124
I don’t know.

13:53.208 --> 13:54.709
You work with him?

13:54.793 --> 13:56.878
I used to.

13:58.964 --> 14:01.550
Jimmy said we’d figure out
where I’m going.

14:01.633 --> 14:03.552
I have a sister
who I can call...

14:03.635 --> 14:05.971
-No sisters, no people.
-How long are we gonna be away?

14:06.054 --> 14:07.931
I don’t know.

14:08.014 --> 14:10.225
So, I’m supposed to live
you don’t know where

14:10.308 --> 14:11.685
for you don’t know how long,

14:11.768 --> 14:13.645
and also you don’t know
if Eddie’s okay.

14:13.728 --> 14:14.896
Just let me call him.

14:14.980 --> 14:16.398
Let him be the one
to explain it.

14:16.481 --> 14:18.024
You can’t.

14:18.108 --> 14:19.234
You’re talking about my husband.

14:19.317 --> 14:21.194
No one knows where he is.

14:22.529 --> 14:25.365
You can’t call him, because
no one knows where he is.

14:27.826 --> 14:29.661
Is anybody looking?

14:29.744 --> 14:31.371
Everyone’s looking.

14:32.956 --> 14:35.333
And they’re looking
for you, too.

14:39.296 --> 14:41.423
A nice house.

14:41.506 --> 14:43.133
Near a park.

14:44.593 --> 14:47.012
I like to take walks
with a stroller.

14:49.806 --> 14:51.808
♪ ♪

15:10.035 --> 15:12.037
(quiet chatter)

15:24.090 --> 15:26.092
♪ ♪

15:54.704 --> 15:56.623
Why isn’t it lit?

15:56.706 --> 16:00.085
("My Life Depends on You" by The
Passionettes playing over radio)

16:00.168 --> 16:02.587
I’ve been told
it isn’t good for me.

16:06.174 --> 16:08.176
So, what’s the point?

16:12.681 --> 16:14.349
It helps.

16:15.433 --> 16:17.143
-(Harry fussing)
-(water running)

16:22.732 --> 16:24.359
(knob creaks, water stops)

16:26.861 --> 16:28.863
-(sighs): Oh, thank God.
-(door opens)

16:37.247 --> 16:39.165
He seemed like...

16:39.249 --> 16:41.084
He’s fine now.

16:42.127 --> 16:44.045
Good thing he’s drinking.

16:44.129 --> 16:46.131
(Harry crying)

16:49.300 --> 16:51.261
(crying stops)

16:51.344 --> 16:55.807
If it’s easier to feed him,
you know, without...

16:55.890 --> 16:57.225
I can step out.

16:57.308 --> 16:59.310
What do you mean?

17:01.146 --> 17:02.939
Uh...

17:03.022 --> 17:04.941
Oh.

17:05.024 --> 17:06.526
It’s fine.

17:06.609 --> 17:09.279
He’s fine. See?

17:19.748 --> 17:21.750
(Harry crying)

17:25.920 --> 17:27.338
-Cal?
-What? What is it?

17:27.422 --> 17:29.758
It’s Harry.
Something’s wrong.

17:29.841 --> 17:32.093
He’s burning up. Feel.

17:32.177 --> 17:34.721
I think we need to go
to a hospital.

17:34.804 --> 17:36.222
No.

17:36.306 --> 17:38.099
No people.
People ask questions.

17:38.183 --> 17:40.101
Hospitals need information.

17:40.185 --> 17:42.812
What part of "everyone’s looking
for you" don’t you understand?

17:42.896 --> 17:45.106
We can’t, Jean.

17:45.190 --> 17:47.150
(quiet chatter in distance)

17:49.903 --> 17:51.529
(Harry cooing)

17:51.613 --> 17:53.364
MAN (over TV):
The, um, uh, star’s partner

17:53.448 --> 17:55.325
of the team that wins, uh,

17:55.408 --> 17:57.452
two out of three rounds
gets to stay on.

17:57.535 --> 17:59.454
-If you understand that,
you’re better than I.
-(man laughs)

17:59.537 --> 18:00.789
Now, they, uh,
what-what they really mean

18:00.872 --> 18:02.499
is that you
and the star’s partner,

18:02.582 --> 18:04.626
and you, Patty,
and the star’s partner,

18:04.709 --> 18:07.796
you get to stay on
if you win the next round.

18:07.879 --> 18:09.380
He stays, and you stay, too.

18:09.464 --> 18:11.090
-You like that arrangement,
I can tell.
-(laughter)

18:11.174 --> 18:14.093
Uh, see, but if you don’t win,

18:14.177 --> 18:16.095
-you go, she stays.
-(phone ringing in distance)

18:16.179 --> 18:18.181
(TV chatter continues
indistinctly)

18:23.436 --> 18:25.688
(laughter over TV)

18:25.772 --> 18:27.690
(TV chatter continues
indistinctly)

18:27.774 --> 18:29.776
(people coughing nearby)

18:46.167 --> 18:48.169
♪ ♪

18:58.638 --> 19:00.723
(footsteps approaching)

19:00.807 --> 19:02.433
CAL (hushed):
Jean.

19:04.060 --> 19:06.062
(footsteps passing)

19:23.746 --> 19:25.665
-(quiet chatter)
-(Harry cooing)

19:25.748 --> 19:27.709
♪ ♪

19:36.134 --> 19:38.136
-(typewriters clicking)
-(phone ringing)

19:42.140 --> 19:44.142
(Harry crying)

19:48.271 --> 19:50.690
-Shh.
-NURSE: Sir?

19:50.773 --> 19:52.859
Ma’am?

19:53.902 --> 19:55.653
Sir?

19:55.737 --> 19:56.905
(elevator bell dings)

19:56.988 --> 19:58.907
(indistinct
police radio chatter)

19:58.990 --> 20:00.992
(officers talking quietly)

20:04.287 --> 20:06.497
-(Jean grunts)
-Excuse me. Sorry.

20:10.585 --> 20:12.211
Don’t look back.

20:14.255 --> 20:15.965
(tires screeching)

20:16.049 --> 20:18.176
("Hold On to the Good Times"
by Peter Dugdale playing)

20:18.259 --> 20:19.802
♪ Morning ♪

20:19.886 --> 20:22.639
♪ Sleepy eyes awake ♪

20:22.722 --> 20:25.808
♪ And with your gentle arms
remind me ♪

20:25.892 --> 20:28.770
♪ You are there ♪

20:28.853 --> 20:30.939
(tires screeching)

20:31.022 --> 20:33.066
♪ Long weekends ♪

20:33.149 --> 20:37.195
♪ Tasting sunshine
by the sea... ♪

20:38.279 --> 20:40.281
(birds chirping)

20:43.576 --> 20:44.994
(knocking on glass)

20:50.541 --> 20:52.835
(indistinct
police radio chatter)

20:54.295 --> 20:56.172
Ma’am, are you all right?

20:56.255 --> 20:57.465
What?

21:00.176 --> 21:01.594
(whispers):
Feel.

21:03.638 --> 21:05.431
It broke.

21:05.515 --> 21:06.683
OFFICER:
Excuse me?

21:08.518 --> 21:11.229
The baby-- he had a fever,
but he’s feeling much cool...

21:11.312 --> 21:13.773
-Get out of the car.
-What’s the problem?

21:13.856 --> 21:14.941
Get out of the car.

21:15.024 --> 21:17.026
But, sir, the baby’s sleeping.

21:19.112 --> 21:21.239
Wait. Cal.

21:21.322 --> 21:22.740
Cal.

21:27.954 --> 21:29.205
I don’t understand
what’s happening.

21:29.288 --> 21:30.707
Just do what he says.

21:30.790 --> 21:32.291
Are you sure you’re all right?

21:32.375 --> 21:33.918
Yes.

21:34.002 --> 21:36.254
This man isn’t bothering you?

21:38.297 --> 21:41.175
Ma’am, why are you
with this man?

21:41.259 --> 21:42.635
He’s my husband.

21:44.721 --> 21:46.514
(officer clears throat)

21:49.809 --> 21:51.853
Is there a problem?

21:53.896 --> 21:56.232
Why were you sleeping
in your car?

21:56.315 --> 21:57.650
We’re sorry, Officer.
We had just...

21:57.734 --> 21:59.736
I’m asking her.

22:06.075 --> 22:08.036
We’re moving to a new house,

22:08.119 --> 22:10.705
and we were so excited,

22:10.788 --> 22:13.791
we wanted to drive all night
and sleep there.

22:13.875 --> 22:15.501
But then, around...

22:17.086 --> 22:18.880
I don’t know, around...

22:18.963 --> 22:20.923
What time was it again, dear?

22:22.383 --> 22:24.302
Uh, a-around 1:00 or 2:00?

22:24.385 --> 22:25.386
That’s right.

22:25.470 --> 22:28.181
Around 1:00 or 2:00,
he started to get tired,

22:28.264 --> 22:31.350
and I was so worried with the
baby and everything, his fever,

22:31.434 --> 22:33.352
so I made him pull over
right away.

22:33.436 --> 22:35.813
I didn’t even want him
driving to a motel.

22:35.897 --> 22:37.899
It’s my fault, Officer.

22:40.735 --> 22:42.737
Do you have kids?

22:45.490 --> 22:48.701
Well, then you know
how mothers can be.

22:51.245 --> 22:53.498
It won’t happen again,
I promise.

23:00.254 --> 23:01.881
Make sure it doesn’t.

23:13.893 --> 23:15.895
(indistinct
police radio chatter)

23:17.897 --> 23:19.524
(engine starts)

23:35.748 --> 23:38.167
I didn’t know
that I could lie like that.

23:43.923 --> 23:45.341
What?

23:48.094 --> 23:49.512
What?

23:53.599 --> 23:55.434
I made a white baby.

24:05.778 --> 24:07.822
(engine starts)

24:07.905 --> 24:09.907
♪ ♪

24:20.918 --> 24:22.920
(dog barking in distance)

24:30.845 --> 24:32.847
(brakes squeaking softly)

24:35.933 --> 24:37.935
♪ ♪

24:59.999 --> 25:01.626
Kitchen’s stocked.

25:03.211 --> 25:05.630
There’s, uh, milk.

25:07.215 --> 25:09.258
Eggs.

25:09.342 --> 25:10.968
Bread.

25:12.428 --> 25:14.055
Some bananas.

25:15.264 --> 25:16.891
Crackers.

25:18.726 --> 25:20.353
And pasta.

25:24.815 --> 25:26.817
And a dining room.

25:38.371 --> 25:39.997
And television.

25:44.001 --> 25:47.505
Your room and the baby’s room
are all set upstairs.

25:47.588 --> 25:49.924
The formula you asked for,
diapers,

25:50.007 --> 25:52.009
and some medicine
if he gets sick again.

25:53.928 --> 25:55.263
There’s a telephone
in the drawer

25:55.346 --> 25:57.098
of your nightstand upstairs.

25:57.181 --> 25:58.516
In an emergency,

25:58.599 --> 26:02.478
-you take it out, plug it in,
-(paper rustling)

26:02.561 --> 26:04.188
and call this number.

26:07.275 --> 26:08.901
Okay?

26:11.070 --> 26:13.614
And you’re not to talk
to anyone.

26:13.698 --> 26:15.449
No friends, no acquaintances.

26:15.533 --> 26:17.743
And make sure
and keep the door locked.

26:17.827 --> 26:19.370
Why are you telling me
everything like...

26:19.453 --> 26:21.372
I’ll be back when I can.

26:21.455 --> 26:22.748
When you can?

26:22.832 --> 26:23.916
When do we get to go home?

26:24.000 --> 26:25.293
I need you to be patient,
all right?

26:25.376 --> 26:27.295
-But Jimmy said you were
gonna help us get set up.
-Jean.

26:27.378 --> 26:29.505
And I’ve never been on my own.

26:29.588 --> 26:31.340
I-I just need a minute to...

26:31.424 --> 26:33.426
This is the way
things have to be.

26:36.846 --> 26:38.973
But Eddie would want you
to stay with us.

26:39.056 --> 26:41.058
I’m doing the best I can!

26:49.400 --> 26:52.194
Let’s both just do
the best we can.

27:07.710 --> 27:09.545
Who did all this?

27:10.796 --> 27:13.007
Eddie still has friends,
I guess.

27:13.090 --> 27:15.718
What do you mean "still"?

27:20.348 --> 27:22.099
Cal.

27:40.951 --> 27:42.953
What about the park?

27:44.538 --> 27:46.165
There is no park.

27:55.633 --> 27:58.886
(car door opens, closes)

27:58.969 --> 28:00.596
(engine starts)

28:02.556 --> 28:04.558
(car drives off)

28:05.893 --> 28:09.188
("Glad and Sorry"
by Faces playing)

28:09.271 --> 28:11.232
(TV playing quietly)

28:24.578 --> 28:27.206
♪ Thank you kindly ♪

28:30.126 --> 28:32.336
♪ For thinking of me ♪

28:35.714 --> 28:37.258
♪ If I’m not smiling ♪

28:37.341 --> 28:39.260
(TV playing quietly)

28:39.343 --> 28:41.554
♪ I’m just thinking ♪

28:53.232 --> 28:54.775
♪ Glad and sorry ♪

28:54.859 --> 28:56.861
(Harry crying)

28:59.071 --> 29:00.823
♪ Happy or sad ♪

29:00.906 --> 29:03.659
(cooing)

29:03.742 --> 29:07.496
♪ When all is done and spoken ♪

29:07.580 --> 29:10.082
♪ You’re up or I’m down ♪

29:11.125 --> 29:13.127
(song continues over radio)

29:19.800 --> 29:21.302
(Harry fussing upstairs)

29:21.385 --> 29:24.138
♪ Can you show me a dream? ♪

29:25.848 --> 29:28.267
-♪ Can you show me one... ♪
-(turns off volume)

29:29.518 --> 29:30.519
(Harry fussing)

29:30.603 --> 29:32.605
(crickets chirping)

29:50.789 --> 29:52.791
♪ ♪

30:20.945 --> 30:22.947
♪ ♪

30:26.534 --> 30:28.536
(gears winding softly)

30:57.690 --> 30:59.108
(plug clicks)

31:21.797 --> 31:23.799
(dial tone humming)

31:34.226 --> 31:35.269
(loud tone beeps)

31:38.939 --> 31:40.941
-(TV playing in other room)
-(Harry grunting)

31:48.741 --> 31:50.743
(clock ticking)

32:03.756 --> 32:05.174
(knocking on door)

32:09.720 --> 32:11.138
(softly):
Hello?

32:13.098 --> 32:15.267
-(knocking on door)
-WOMAN: Hello?

32:15.351 --> 32:17.019
It’s your neighbor.

32:18.062 --> 32:19.271
(key clicks in lock)

32:22.316 --> 32:23.734
Hi.

32:25.736 --> 32:27.905
-Is everything all right?
-Yes.

32:27.988 --> 32:28.989
Of course.

32:29.073 --> 32:30.699
(laughs):
Oh, no, I...

32:30.783 --> 32:32.660
I didn’t mean to frighten you.

32:32.743 --> 32:36.121
M-My friends lived
in this house for years.

32:36.205 --> 32:38.874
It’s nice to see
someone new here.

32:41.919 --> 32:43.921
I’m Evelyn.

32:47.883 --> 32:49.301
Mary.

32:49.385 --> 32:51.887
Nice to meet you, Mary.

32:51.970 --> 32:54.014
Um, I live, uh, two doors down.

32:55.057 --> 32:58.268
My husband passed
a few years ago.

32:58.352 --> 33:02.523
Uh, but if you ever need
any help or anything...

33:05.150 --> 33:07.069
Oh.

33:07.152 --> 33:08.654
Thank you.

33:14.702 --> 33:16.328
All right.

33:18.706 --> 33:19.707
Goodbye.

33:19.790 --> 33:21.291
Oh, what’s your baby’s name?

33:21.375 --> 33:24.586
-Harry.
-Harry.

33:24.670 --> 33:25.713
(chuckles)

33:25.796 --> 33:27.589
Oh.

33:27.673 --> 33:29.258
Harry and Mary.

33:55.784 --> 33:57.786
♪ ♪

34:23.604 --> 34:25.606
♪ ♪

34:38.994 --> 34:40.996
(exhales slowly)

35:02.976 --> 35:04.978
(crying)

35:33.841 --> 35:35.259
(sighs softly)

35:42.558 --> 35:44.977
(clock ticking)

35:55.404 --> 35:56.822
(knocking on door)

36:03.078 --> 36:04.663
Candygram.

36:04.746 --> 36:05.956
(chuckling softly)

36:10.919 --> 36:14.923
But when my daughter moved away,
it was hard again.

36:16.133 --> 36:18.385
Hmm.

36:18.468 --> 36:22.556
When the television’s on,
I forget I’m alone.

36:22.639 --> 36:23.807
(chuckles)

36:29.146 --> 36:31.023
This was delicious.

36:31.106 --> 36:32.608
Oh, it’s easy.

36:32.691 --> 36:35.193
I’ll give you the recipe.

36:35.277 --> 36:37.112
I’m a terrible cook.

36:46.580 --> 36:48.957
Do you mind me asking--

36:49.041 --> 36:51.585
is Harry sleeping
through the night?

36:51.668 --> 36:54.129
I’m sorry.

36:54.212 --> 36:56.131
D-Do you hear him crying?
I’m-I’m trying to keep him...

36:56.214 --> 36:58.133
Oh, no, no, dear.

36:58.216 --> 37:00.218
(sighs) It’s just...

37:03.013 --> 37:05.682
You seem exhausted.

37:11.813 --> 37:13.440
(softly):
I’m so tired.

37:16.068 --> 37:18.487
I’m so tired all the time.

37:21.198 --> 37:24.451
I swear I hear him crying
when he’s asleep.

37:31.750 --> 37:34.169
What happened to your husband?

37:44.721 --> 37:46.473
Uh... (sighs)

37:46.556 --> 37:47.641
I’m prying.

37:47.724 --> 37:48.809
(scoffs softly)

37:48.892 --> 37:50.310
I just...

37:51.603 --> 37:52.729
(sighs)

37:52.813 --> 37:54.314
Where’s your bathroom?

37:54.398 --> 37:57.359
Upstairs at the end of the hall.

38:02.364 --> 38:04.741
Didn’t you say your friends
used to live here?

38:04.825 --> 38:06.910
Pardon?

38:06.994 --> 38:08.912
You said
your friends lived here.

38:08.996 --> 38:10.998
-The bathroom.
-Gosh, no.

38:11.081 --> 38:12.666
You’re right.

38:16.670 --> 38:19.673
I guess I’m getting old
faster than I thought.

38:28.432 --> 38:30.434
(footsteps ascending stairs)

38:53.582 --> 38:55.584
-Evelyn?
-(silverware clatters on floor)

38:59.379 --> 39:01.381
-Evel...
-(footsteps descending stairs)

39:04.009 --> 39:06.011
Are you all right?

39:08.680 --> 39:10.432
(key clicks in lock)

39:12.726 --> 39:14.352
Good night.

39:25.655 --> 39:27.657
(Harry crying)

39:36.833 --> 39:38.835
(crickets chirping)

39:54.976 --> 39:56.728
-(door closes in distance)
-(distant shouting)

39:56.812 --> 39:58.814
(dog barking in distance)

40:28.176 --> 40:29.594
(Harry fusses quietly)

40:55.162 --> 40:56.705
(footsteps creaking)

40:56.788 --> 40:58.790
(objects rummaging)

41:03.336 --> 41:05.338
♪ ♪

41:09.676 --> 41:11.678
(panting)

41:14.723 --> 41:16.725
(Harry fussing quietly)

41:18.935 --> 41:20.937
(Jean shushing)

41:29.112 --> 41:31.114
(panting)

41:42.000 --> 41:44.002
(Harry fussing quietly)

41:58.225 --> 42:00.143
(shushing)

42:00.227 --> 42:02.229
♪ ♪

42:32.259 --> 42:34.261
♪ ♪

42:40.267 --> 42:42.185
(dial tone humming)

42:42.269 --> 42:44.271
(beeping)

42:48.149 --> 42:51.278
(line ringing)

42:51.361 --> 42:53.363
(whispering):
Pick up, pick up, pick up.

42:54.489 --> 42:56.491
-(line clicks)
-Hello.

43:02.080 --> 43:03.290
Hello?

43:06.710 --> 43:08.128
(dial tone humming)

43:11.798 --> 43:13.717
(panting)

43:13.800 --> 43:15.719
(steady tone beeping)

43:15.802 --> 43:17.220
Shit.

43:20.056 --> 43:22.058
(footsteps outside room)

43:26.313 --> 43:28.148
♪ ♪

43:28.231 --> 43:30.233
(Harry crying)

43:50.545 --> 43:52.547
(crying continues)

43:56.718 --> 43:58.136
Evelyn?

44:05.769 --> 44:07.520
Evelyn?

44:07.604 --> 44:09.773
-Evelyn, I know that this is...
-Jean.

44:10.815 --> 44:11.858
Sit down.

44:11.941 --> 44:14.694
(crying continues)

44:16.154 --> 44:18.490
Ah, tut-tut-tut-tut.

44:18.573 --> 44:20.575
(panting)

44:24.704 --> 44:26.289
♪ ♪

44:26.373 --> 44:28.333
(crying continues)

44:36.049 --> 44:37.926
(shushes)

44:52.440 --> 44:54.692
Where’s Eddie?

44:57.737 --> 44:59.406
We know you know.

44:59.489 --> 45:01.366
I don’t know anything.

45:01.449 --> 45:03.076
(crying continues)

45:03.159 --> 45:05.078
Shut the kid up.

45:06.663 --> 45:08.706
-What the fuck is wrong with it?
-I have to stand up.

45:08.790 --> 45:10.625
-No, you stay the fuck down.
-I-I have to rock him.

45:10.708 --> 45:12.419
-Please just let me stand up.
-No, absol...

45:12.502 --> 45:14.504
(crying continues)

45:15.630 --> 45:17.632
(crying quiets)

45:19.467 --> 45:21.386
-(door opens)
-(gunshots)

45:21.469 --> 45:24.180
(Harry crying)

45:30.854 --> 45:32.981
(muffled whimpering)

45:33.064 --> 45:34.149
It’s okay.

45:34.232 --> 45:35.608
Cover his ears.

45:35.692 --> 45:36.693
-Wait.
-(muffled scream)

45:36.776 --> 45:37.777
(gunshot)

45:37.861 --> 45:39.779
(Harry continues crying)

45:46.035 --> 45:48.121
-You can’t just kill someone.
-Someone who what, Jean?

45:48.204 --> 45:49.581
I didn’t, I didn’t want
to do that.

45:49.664 --> 45:51.332
-We could’ve explained...
-I didn’t want
to do any of that.

45:51.416 --> 45:53.168
-We could have told her...
-She saw me kill those men!

45:53.251 --> 45:54.627
-She was innocent.
-How do you know?

45:54.711 --> 45:56.129
She was an innocent--
How do I know what?

45:56.212 --> 45:57.380
God, she might have
worked for them.

45:57.464 --> 45:58.840
-She might have tipped them off.
-It’s not possible.

45:58.923 --> 46:01.259
Are you really gonna tell me the
thought didn’t cross your mind?

46:01.342 --> 46:03.470
-(Harry continues crying)
-(Jean panting)

46:03.553 --> 46:05.263
-But what if she was innocent?
-She-she was dead.

46:05.346 --> 46:07.599
She was dead the moment
you invited her in.

46:07.682 --> 46:10.602
I told you, no people.

46:10.685 --> 46:12.437
-Try the finger.
-It won’t work.

46:12.520 --> 46:14.647
-It always works.
-Not if he’s hungry.

46:14.731 --> 46:16.149
-He’s hungry?
-Yeah.

46:16.232 --> 46:18.276
-Then fucking feed him!
-I can’t!

46:18.359 --> 46:19.736
What? Are-are you serious, Jean?

46:19.819 --> 46:22.238
-It’s nothing
I haven’t seen before.
-I can’t.

46:23.490 --> 46:24.699
(shushing quietly)

46:26.284 --> 46:28.203
(Harry fussing)

46:28.286 --> 46:30.288
(register beeping)

46:33.917 --> 46:35.919
(Harry crying)

46:40.465 --> 46:42.467
(Harry cooing)

46:50.642 --> 46:52.644
(traffic passing in distance)

47:21.256 --> 47:23.341
I can’t have children.

47:25.510 --> 47:27.470
Eddie said he didn’t care.

47:27.554 --> 47:30.223
That wasn’t why he wanted me.

47:30.306 --> 47:33.643
He said he loved me
and we would figure it out.

47:35.645 --> 47:39.399
But we couldn’t adopt
’cause of his record.

47:41.401 --> 47:43.027
Obviously.

47:47.365 --> 47:50.410
And then, one day,
he walks in with a baby.

47:54.163 --> 47:56.165
I said, "Who is that?"

47:59.168 --> 48:02.505
Eddie smiles and says,

48:02.589 --> 48:04.591
"He’s our baby."

48:13.641 --> 48:16.269
This girl was in trouble.

48:16.352 --> 48:18.479
Eddie paid for everything.

48:18.563 --> 48:20.189
Best doctors, all of it.

48:20.273 --> 48:24.611
Her father was gonna disown her,
but Eddie put it right.

48:27.739 --> 48:30.867
Eddie said everybody’s life
got saved that day.

48:41.169 --> 48:43.296
I think about his mother.

48:47.425 --> 48:49.427
I think about her all the time.

48:55.433 --> 48:57.518
Do you have anyone?

48:57.602 --> 48:59.228
(chuckles):
What?

49:02.148 --> 49:04.150
You wouldn’t tell me anyway.

49:08.237 --> 49:10.365
Once I found out
I couldn’t have a kid,

49:10.448 --> 49:13.284
I stopped wanting it.

49:13.368 --> 49:14.952
Thought maybe
it would be better.

49:17.914 --> 49:20.875
I shouldn’t bring a baby
into a life like this.

49:21.918 --> 49:23.920
Eddie’s a criminal.

49:26.005 --> 49:29.467
I told myself
that’s why I kept losing them.

49:31.052 --> 49:33.471
That’s why they wouldn’t
stay with me.

49:41.062 --> 49:43.231
But I really did want it.

49:45.733 --> 49:47.735
More than anything.

49:51.030 --> 49:53.908
I just had to keep living,
you know?

49:53.991 --> 49:56.703
So I burned it all up.

49:58.454 --> 50:02.041
I burned it up till there was
nothing left but the fire.

50:07.130 --> 50:09.757
And then in walked Eddie
with a baby.

50:14.470 --> 50:16.389
(sniffles softly)

50:16.472 --> 50:17.890
(sighs)

50:17.974 --> 50:20.643
This is no place for a child.

50:20.727 --> 50:21.936
(sniffling)

50:27.400 --> 50:29.193
D-Does he laugh?

50:29.277 --> 50:31.320
What?

50:31.404 --> 50:32.989
Do you make him laugh?

50:33.072 --> 50:35.450
What the hell
are you talking about?

50:35.533 --> 50:37.452
If you’ve heard him laugh.

50:37.535 --> 50:39.537
You know.

50:39.620 --> 50:42.039
Course I’ve heard him laugh.

50:42.123 --> 50:43.958
Well, then you know.

50:49.464 --> 50:51.090
He laughs.

50:54.552 --> 50:56.554
Especially when I...

50:58.681 --> 51:00.349
What?

51:00.433 --> 51:01.642
(sniffles)

51:01.726 --> 51:03.227
When what?

51:06.856 --> 51:08.274
(sighs softly)

51:10.651 --> 51:13.946
I do this thing
when I’m singing.

51:14.030 --> 51:16.032
I don’t know-- he likes it.

51:16.115 --> 51:18.826
It happened and it worked,
so I kept doing it.

51:18.910 --> 51:21.496
It’s not even
a song about babies.

51:24.373 --> 51:26.125
And now that
I’m talking about it,

51:26.209 --> 51:28.920
I’m realizing
it’s actually pretty weird.

51:29.003 --> 51:31.297
Do it.

51:31.380 --> 51:33.424
He’s asleep.

51:33.508 --> 51:34.884
I’ll get the idea.

51:34.967 --> 51:36.177
Absolutely not.

51:36.260 --> 51:38.554
Fine.

51:38.638 --> 51:39.931
If you’re too chicken.

51:40.014 --> 51:41.808
♪ Looking out ♪

51:41.891 --> 51:44.519
♪ On the morning rain ♪

51:47.605 --> 51:48.940
(deeply):
♪ A-whoo ♪

51:49.023 --> 51:50.858
(laughs)

51:50.942 --> 51:55.363
♪ I used to feel so uninspired ♪

51:57.156 --> 51:58.241
(softly):
♪ A-whoo ♪

51:59.367 --> 52:01.077
♪ And when I knew ♪

52:01.160 --> 52:05.373
♪ I had to face another day ♪

52:05.456 --> 52:07.959
♪ A-whoo ♪

52:08.042 --> 52:11.587
♪ Lord, it made me feel
so tired ♪

52:12.755 --> 52:15.216
♪ Before the day I met you ♪

52:15.299 --> 52:19.178
♪ Life was so unkind ♪

52:19.262 --> 52:24.725
♪ You’re the key
