♪ I didn’t know
just what was wrong with me ♪

54:02.406 --> 54:03.532
♪ Ah-ooh ♪

54:03.616 --> 54:08.037
♪ Till your kiss
helped me name it ♪

54:09.830 --> 54:11.666
♪ Now I’m no longer doubt... ♪

54:13.584 --> 54:14.794
CAL:
Okay?

54:16.128 --> 54:18.214
There’s a first time
for everything.

54:22.176 --> 54:26.681
There’s, uh, some more cans in
the pantry once this runs out.

54:29.600 --> 54:31.519
Some old clothes
in the wardrobe.

54:31.602 --> 54:33.145
There’s a water pump out there,

54:33.229 --> 54:36.357
enough wood out on
the side of the house for now.

54:36.440 --> 54:38.359
There’s no phone.

54:38.442 --> 54:41.570
There’s never been any trouble,
but just in case...

54:41.654 --> 54:43.656
Move that chair.

54:49.412 --> 54:51.414
Move that one back.

54:54.083 --> 54:56.293
Grab the table,
move it that way.

55:19.817 --> 55:22.445
It was my hiding place.

55:22.528 --> 55:24.572
When I was a kid.

55:27.575 --> 55:29.452
This was your family’s.

55:32.496 --> 55:34.832
I’ll be back soon.

55:34.915 --> 55:37.626
-You’re not gonna leave me.
-Do you have a better idea?

55:37.710 --> 55:40.629
What about the money
at the house?

55:40.713 --> 55:42.381
That money’s gone, Jean.

55:42.465 --> 55:44.300
Don’t you have money?

55:44.383 --> 55:46.427
-Like Eddie?
-(sighs)

55:46.510 --> 55:49.180
I worked for Eddie.

55:49.263 --> 55:50.890
I’m not Eddie.

55:50.973 --> 55:52.808
So, what am I, a chore?

55:52.892 --> 55:54.727
-(table scrapes on floor)
-Shh.

55:54.810 --> 55:56.854
(Harry fussing quietly)

56:09.325 --> 56:11.327
This isn’t about you, Jean.

56:18.250 --> 56:20.002
Eddie killed the boss.

56:20.086 --> 56:21.879
Marvin.

56:21.962 --> 56:24.173
The night we left.

56:24.256 --> 56:28.761
Then Marvin’s guys went over
to your place, killed Jimmy.

56:28.844 --> 56:30.971
Now no one knows what’s what.

56:31.055 --> 56:32.473
It’s just...

56:32.556 --> 56:34.391
The city’s chaos.

56:36.435 --> 56:38.312
That’s all I know.

56:42.942 --> 56:44.944
Eddie would never kill anyone.

56:48.739 --> 56:50.157
(sighs softly)

56:52.201 --> 56:54.203
Eddie’s a killer, Jean.

56:55.955 --> 56:57.957
He has been for a long time.

57:11.303 --> 57:14.014
Where is he now?

57:14.098 --> 57:15.724
I don’t know.

57:18.727 --> 57:20.354
You swear?

57:24.817 --> 57:26.861
I-I really don’t know.

57:51.844 --> 57:53.846
You do have someone.

57:58.309 --> 58:00.978
The someone who told you
those weren’t good for you.

58:02.813 --> 58:05.816
And they told you that
because they love you.

58:23.792 --> 58:26.003
He didn’t have a name.

58:29.256 --> 58:30.883
Harry.

58:32.259 --> 58:34.261
I named him Harry.

58:37.389 --> 58:40.434
No reason.
I-I just liked the name.

58:43.395 --> 58:47.024
When I was pregnant the longest,
I named the baby Harry.

58:51.320 --> 58:53.781
-I never told anyone.
-(Harry crying)

59:06.335 --> 59:08.796
(Harry continues crying)

59:10.673 --> 59:12.174
(door opens)

59:12.258 --> 59:14.677
How long do you think
it’s gonna be until...

59:16.262 --> 59:17.596
-(wind whistling)
-(car door closes)

59:17.680 --> 59:18.806
(engine starts)

59:24.103 --> 59:26.105
(car driving on gravel)

59:31.026 --> 59:32.736
(brakes squeak softly)

59:33.779 --> 59:35.781
(car driving off)

59:41.120 --> 59:43.080
(Harry continues crying)

59:43.163 --> 59:45.833
("Follow" by Richie Havens
playing)

59:56.677 --> 59:58.595
♪ Let the river ♪

59:58.679 --> 1:00:01.890
♪ Rock you like a cradle ♪

1:00:03.434 --> 1:00:06.312
♪ Climb to the treetops ♪

1:00:06.395 --> 1:00:08.814
♪ Child, if you’re able ♪

1:00:10.524 --> 1:00:12.860
♪ Let your hands ♪

1:00:12.943 --> 1:00:15.946
♪ Tie a knot across the table ♪

1:00:18.240 --> 1:00:20.451
♪ Come and touch ♪

1:00:20.534 --> 1:00:23.370
♪ The things you cannot feel ♪

1:00:24.788 --> 1:00:28.625
♪ And close your fingertips ♪

1:00:28.709 --> 1:00:32.087
♪ And fly
where I can’t hold you ♪

1:00:33.255 --> 1:00:35.841
♪ Let the sun-rain fall ♪

1:00:35.924 --> 1:00:40.220
-(Harry crying)
-♪ And let the dewy clouds
enfold you ♪

1:00:40.304 --> 1:00:43.724
♪ And maybe you can sing to me ♪

1:00:43.807 --> 1:00:47.519
♪ The words I just told you ♪

1:00:47.603 --> 1:00:51.732
♪ If all the things you feel
ain’t what they seem ♪

1:00:51.815 --> 1:00:53.233
(crying quiets)

1:00:53.317 --> 1:00:57.196
♪ Then don’t mind me ♪

1:00:57.279 --> 1:01:03.285
♪ ’Cause I ain’t nothing
but a dream ♪

1:01:04.536 --> 1:01:06.538
(song continues over radio)

1:01:08.665 --> 1:01:13.128
♪ The mockingbird sings
each different song ♪

1:01:14.797 --> 1:01:18.133
♪ Each song has wings ♪

1:01:18.217 --> 1:01:20.427
♪ They won’t stay long ♪

1:01:21.470 --> 1:01:24.098
♪ Do those who hear... ♪

1:01:24.181 --> 1:01:26.642
Fire.

1:01:26.725 --> 1:01:29.186
Hot.

1:01:29.269 --> 1:01:31.522
Yeah.

1:01:31.605 --> 1:01:33.565
Fire.

1:01:33.649 --> 1:01:36.151
F... F...

1:01:36.235 --> 1:01:38.487
Fire.

1:01:39.988 --> 1:01:41.407
Hot.

1:01:43.826 --> 1:01:46.453
♪ Come here where your ears... ♪

1:01:46.537 --> 1:01:48.705
I did that.

1:01:51.542 --> 1:01:53.377
I did it.

1:01:53.460 --> 1:01:55.462
-(Harry cooing)
-(Jean humming softly)

1:01:57.297 --> 1:01:59.299
(whispers):
♪ A-whoo ♪

1:01:59.383 --> 1:02:01.385
(humming softly)

1:02:03.846 --> 1:02:05.681
-(whispers): ♪ A-whoo ♪
-(laughing)

1:02:05.764 --> 1:02:07.766
(humming softly)

1:02:10.978 --> 1:02:12.396
(whispers):
♪ A-whoo ♪

1:02:16.859 --> 1:02:18.318
(blows):
♪ A-whoo ♪

1:02:24.116 --> 1:02:26.118
(cooing softly)

1:02:26.201 --> 1:02:28.203
(vehicle approaching
in distance)

1:02:29.371 --> 1:02:31.373
(birds cawing)

1:02:58.400 --> 1:03:00.068
(panting)

1:03:11.079 --> 1:03:13.499
(car doors closing)

1:03:13.582 --> 1:03:15.584
(man talking outside)

1:03:17.211 --> 1:03:18.837
-(door opens)
-(Jean gasps)

1:03:18.921 --> 1:03:21.840
-(footsteps)
-(Harry fussing)

1:03:21.924 --> 1:03:23.842
BOY:
Mom!

1:03:23.926 --> 1:03:26.637
She found my hiding place.

1:03:27.679 --> 1:03:30.432
She sure did.

1:03:30.516 --> 1:03:31.642
I’m Teri.

1:03:31.725 --> 1:03:33.310
This is Paul.

1:03:33.393 --> 1:03:34.520
And that’s Art.

1:03:34.603 --> 1:03:36.605
(Harry continues fussing)

1:03:42.736 --> 1:03:44.488
I’m sorry. Who...

1:03:45.572 --> 1:03:47.282
Teri.

1:03:47.366 --> 1:03:48.867
Cal’s wife.

1:03:52.204 --> 1:03:54.540
Why don’t you get out of
that hole, help us unpack.

1:03:54.623 --> 1:03:56.625
Hey. Come on, give me a hand.

1:04:02.130 --> 1:04:05.050
And that’s...?

1:04:05.133 --> 1:04:06.552
TERI:
Cal’s dad.

1:04:08.178 --> 1:04:10.180
You’re Eddie’s wife.

1:04:11.390 --> 1:04:13.392
You know Eddie?

1:04:16.019 --> 1:04:17.646
Yeah, I know Eddie.

1:04:17.729 --> 1:04:18.981
(refrigerator opens)

1:04:19.064 --> 1:04:20.983
Paul?

1:04:21.066 --> 1:04:23.652
You run and go check
the wood, baby?

1:04:26.071 --> 1:04:27.489
(door opens)

1:04:29.199 --> 1:04:31.201
-And...
-(door closes)

1:04:31.285 --> 1:04:33.078
Eddie used to work with Cal?

1:04:34.204 --> 1:04:35.789
He wouldn’t tell me much.

1:04:35.872 --> 1:04:37.499
TERI:
Cal’s a smart man.

1:04:37.583 --> 1:04:40.252
-Is Cal...
-He’ll be here.

1:04:40.335 --> 1:04:43.171
-Is he...
-Don’t worry about Cal.

1:04:45.215 --> 1:04:47.092
PAUL (in distance):
Almost out!

1:04:47.175 --> 1:04:48.510
(Art and Paul talking quietly)

1:04:48.594 --> 1:04:50.596
♪ ♪

1:05:12.451 --> 1:05:14.453
(Harry fussing)

1:05:15.871 --> 1:05:17.873
(Harry crying)

1:05:34.097 --> 1:05:35.515
(Art groans softly)

1:05:48.695 --> 1:05:50.614
(crying quiets)

1:05:50.697 --> 1:05:52.699
(Art shushing, whispering)

1:05:54.159 --> 1:05:56.161
(Art talking playfully,
shushing)

1:06:00.332 --> 1:06:02.751
I just want
to get back to sleep.

1:06:04.127 --> 1:06:07.214
Now I know where Cal gets it.

1:06:11.301 --> 1:06:13.303
He’s good with the baby?

1:06:17.224 --> 1:06:21.436
Teri said her first husband
was no good.

1:06:25.232 --> 1:06:27.651
-(Art shushing, whispering)
-(Harry fussing quietly)

1:06:27.734 --> 1:06:29.569
Oh, I was gonna feed him.

1:06:29.653 --> 1:06:30.987
No.

1:06:31.071 --> 1:06:34.074
We don’t eat
in the middle of the night.

1:06:35.283 --> 1:06:37.661
It’s best he learns that.

1:06:41.373 --> 1:06:42.457
Everything all right?

1:06:42.541 --> 1:06:44.418
ART:
Everything’s fine.

1:06:44.501 --> 1:06:46.461
Go back to sleep.

1:06:56.555 --> 1:06:58.473
TERI:
When Paul was little,

1:06:58.557 --> 1:07:03.520
we had to live in this old hotel
in the city for a while.

1:07:03.603 --> 1:07:05.564
The Saint Francis.

1:07:05.647 --> 1:07:07.232
I remember that.

1:07:07.315 --> 1:07:09.317
Why?

1:07:09.401 --> 1:07:11.361
It was safe for us.

1:07:11.445 --> 1:07:14.239
It’s Black-owned,
Black-operated.

1:07:14.322 --> 1:07:16.867
Place where people could go
to fix their lives.

1:07:16.950 --> 1:07:18.493
(music playing quietly
over radio)

1:07:18.577 --> 1:07:21.830
I mean, it was
kind of a in-between place.

1:07:23.331 --> 1:07:25.208
Not quite there yet,

1:07:25.292 --> 1:07:27.502
but better than
where they’d been.

1:07:29.504 --> 1:07:32.424
"Where there is despair,
I may bring hope."

1:07:32.507 --> 1:07:35.510
You know
the Prayer of Saint Francis.

1:07:35.594 --> 1:07:38.513
The one good thing I kept
from Catholic school.

1:07:38.597 --> 1:07:39.848
(Art chuckles)

1:07:39.931 --> 1:07:41.266
Everything smelled old.

1:07:41.349 --> 1:07:44.060
Sometimes the toilets
wouldn’t flush.

1:07:44.144 --> 1:07:45.896
But Paul loved it.

1:07:45.979 --> 1:07:47.564
There was a phone in the hall.

1:07:47.647 --> 1:07:50.317
He’d run to it
every time it rang.

1:07:50.400 --> 1:07:52.944
A little answering service,
up on his tippy-toes.

1:07:53.028 --> 1:07:54.988
(Art chuckles)

1:07:59.951 --> 1:08:01.828
You were hiding.

1:08:01.912 --> 1:08:04.289
ART:
Paul, eat your peas.

1:08:17.302 --> 1:08:19.179
What did you do to the peas?

1:08:19.262 --> 1:08:21.556
Something wrong?

1:08:21.640 --> 1:08:23.975
They’re the ones from the can?

1:08:24.059 --> 1:08:25.143
Yeah.

1:08:27.896 --> 1:08:29.314
They’re delicious.

1:08:29.397 --> 1:08:30.899
(chuckles):
Oh.

1:08:30.982 --> 1:08:32.526
(chuckles softly)

1:08:32.609 --> 1:08:35.654
Salt, pepper, some butter.

1:08:35.737 --> 1:08:38.490
Some love.

1:08:38.573 --> 1:08:41.034
You just heat them up
out of the can?

1:08:41.117 --> 1:08:44.079
I’m a terrible cook.

1:08:44.162 --> 1:08:45.539
You feed your family, yeah?

1:08:45.622 --> 1:08:46.957
Yeah, but...

1:08:47.040 --> 1:08:49.042
Then you’re
the world’s greatest chef.

1:08:55.340 --> 1:08:57.676
ART: I got the place
when Cal was five.

1:08:59.386 --> 1:09:01.680
Are you married?

1:09:01.763 --> 1:09:03.014
I was.

1:09:03.098 --> 1:09:06.101
My wife passed
about four years ago.

1:09:09.104 --> 1:09:11.022
Cal wouldn’t
talk about anything.

1:09:11.106 --> 1:09:14.150
His family or anything.

1:09:14.234 --> 1:09:16.236
Occupational hazard.

1:09:21.283 --> 1:09:23.493
I’m about to take out a gun.

1:09:31.418 --> 1:09:32.836
It’s empty.

1:09:34.546 --> 1:09:36.381
You ever use one?

1:09:39.384 --> 1:09:42.721
All these men
and all their guns.

1:09:42.804 --> 1:09:45.640
My husband wouldn’t even
let me drive the car.

1:09:46.725 --> 1:09:48.852
(chuckles)

1:09:48.935 --> 1:09:53.064
Listen, anyone can
learn to shoot.

1:09:53.148 --> 1:09:57.360
But the hard part is what you
actually do when the time comes.

1:09:58.361 --> 1:10:00.614
Now, when you practice,

1:10:00.697 --> 1:10:02.240
you pull the trigger...

1:10:02.324 --> 1:10:03.992
(gun clicks)

1:10:04.075 --> 1:10:07.704
...and you think about pressure
and alignment.

1:10:09.664 --> 1:10:12.208
But what you really need
to figure out is

1:10:12.292 --> 1:10:14.711
what you’ll do when it’s real.

1:10:19.007 --> 1:10:20.425
Here.

1:10:21.760 --> 1:10:23.386
Get used to the weight.

1:10:39.069 --> 1:10:42.197
-(door opens, closes)
-(footsteps walking quickly)

1:10:42.280 --> 1:10:45.283
JEAN: Why did Art show me
how to use a gun?

1:10:47.202 --> 1:10:50.121
Paul, can you go outside
and find Grandpa?

1:10:56.127 --> 1:10:59.255
(door opens, closes)

1:10:59.339 --> 1:11:01.925
There were some guys
outside our apartment.

1:11:02.008 --> 1:11:04.344
You live in the city?

1:11:04.427 --> 1:11:05.637
Yeah.

1:11:05.720 --> 1:11:07.430
First, I thought
Cal was just paranoid,

1:11:07.514 --> 1:11:11.434
but after two more nights of it,
he packed up and sent us away.

1:11:11.518 --> 1:11:13.395
Said he’d be right behind us.

1:11:13.478 --> 1:11:17.524
I just thought you should be
prepared for what comes next.

1:11:19.192 --> 1:11:20.944
What comes next?

1:11:21.027 --> 1:11:23.238
I don’t know yet.

1:11:23.321 --> 1:11:25.740
But I’ve been
through this before.

1:11:26.825 --> 1:11:28.743
(Harry fussing quietly)

1:11:28.827 --> 1:11:30.495
(Teri shushing)

1:11:33.331 --> 1:11:35.333
(Teri shushing)

1:11:47.637 --> 1:11:50.640
Art said something
the other night.

1:11:52.642 --> 1:11:54.227
What?

1:11:56.271 --> 1:11:58.732
Eddie was your first husband.

1:12:04.320 --> 1:12:05.947
Art told you that?

1:12:08.408 --> 1:12:10.410
I put it together.

1:12:14.372 --> 1:12:16.583
Eddie did the same thing to you?

1:12:16.666 --> 1:12:18.084
Before Cal?

1:12:19.753 --> 1:12:21.921
Except it’s worse
’cause we have a kid.

1:12:22.005 --> 1:12:24.090
Nothing’s worse for you.

1:12:24.174 --> 1:12:26.301
You don’t know that.

1:12:27.385 --> 1:12:29.012
Yeah, I do.

1:12:30.055 --> 1:12:31.681
(Harry fussing quietly)

1:12:39.814 --> 1:12:40.940
(Teri chuckles softly)

1:12:41.024 --> 1:12:43.026
(shushing)

1:12:47.322 --> 1:12:50.325
Eddie never told me
he had another wife.

1:12:54.329 --> 1:12:56.664
He never told me
a lot of things.

1:12:58.291 --> 1:13:00.293
That’s what they do.

1:13:01.503 --> 1:13:03.505
(birds chirping)

1:13:21.689 --> 1:13:23.191
(gun clicking)

1:13:24.943 --> 1:13:26.486
(birds squawking, fluttering)

1:13:26.569 --> 1:13:28.446
(panting)

1:13:53.638 --> 1:13:54.848
(gun clicking)

1:14:28.214 --> 1:14:30.216
♪ ♪

1:14:54.699 --> 1:14:56.576
(Art talking quietly)

1:14:56.659 --> 1:14:58.661
♪ ♪

1:15:21.476 --> 1:15:22.894
(whispering):
Teri.

1:15:24.479 --> 1:15:26.481
Are you awake?

1:15:28.566 --> 1:15:30.985
Something’s not right.

1:15:31.069 --> 1:15:32.570
We should go find Cal.

1:15:32.654 --> 1:15:34.197
We need to find Cal and Eddie.

1:15:34.280 --> 1:15:35.657
You need to stop
worrying about...

1:15:35.740 --> 1:15:38.868
I am so sick of everyone
telling me what to do.

1:15:38.952 --> 1:15:40.954
(Jean panting)

1:15:42.372 --> 1:15:44.499
(Teri sighs)

1:15:44.582 --> 1:15:46.000
What?

1:15:47.543 --> 1:15:48.586
What?

1:15:48.670 --> 1:15:50.588
I was gonna leave.

1:15:50.672 --> 1:15:53.466
I was gonna leave when
I was sure you were all asleep.

1:15:53.549 --> 1:15:56.427
Of course I know
Cal’s in trouble.

1:15:56.511 --> 1:15:58.846
Sorry.

1:15:58.930 --> 1:16:00.932
Art was gonna tell you
in the morning.

1:16:02.934 --> 1:16:04.310
I’m going with you.

1:16:04.394 --> 1:16:05.937
And you can’t stop me.

1:16:06.020 --> 1:16:07.730
No one can give me
a straight answer

1:16:07.814 --> 1:16:10.316
about what I’m supposed to do
or where I’m supposed to be,

1:16:10.400 --> 1:16:12.360
and it’s because
there is no answer.

1:16:12.443 --> 1:16:14.737
No one knows anything.

1:16:14.821 --> 1:16:17.073
So I’m doing this.
I’m coming.

1:16:18.449 --> 1:16:20.076
I’m coming.

1:16:22.912 --> 1:16:24.539
Are you done?

1:16:26.124 --> 1:16:27.875
-Yes.
-All right.

1:16:27.959 --> 1:16:29.294
All right, I’m coming?

1:16:29.377 --> 1:16:31.379
You already told me you were.

1:16:33.715 --> 1:16:35.925
Okay.

1:16:36.009 --> 1:16:38.011
♪ ♪

1:16:50.940 --> 1:16:52.358
(kisses)

1:17:11.044 --> 1:17:13.046
♪ ♪

1:17:26.809 --> 1:17:28.811
(engine idling)

1:17:58.841 --> 1:18:00.843
♪ ♪

1:18:29.705 --> 1:18:31.082
(siren wailing in distance)

1:18:31.165 --> 1:18:35.002
Those two dark windows--
that’s our apartment.

1:18:36.045 --> 1:18:38.631
We usually leave a light on.

1:18:48.266 --> 1:18:51.769
(glove compartment
opens, closes)

1:18:52.854 --> 1:18:54.856
Put this in your pocket.

1:18:56.107 --> 1:18:58.109
So you always know it’s there.

1:19:00.528 --> 1:19:03.156
We have to go somewhere.

1:19:03.239 --> 1:19:06.242
And when we’re there, I need you
to listen to me, okay?

1:19:09.245 --> 1:19:11.414
You can’t tell anyone
who you are.

1:19:11.497 --> 1:19:13.749
It’s not a safe place for us.

1:19:17.670 --> 1:19:19.380
And we’re gonna need
some different clothes.

1:19:21.883 --> 1:19:23.593
(engine starts)

1:19:23.676 --> 1:19:25.595
("Don’t Stop"
by Spaceark playing)

1:19:25.678 --> 1:19:27.680
(lively chatter)

1:19:30.892 --> 1:19:32.518
♪ Don’t stop ♪

1:19:34.187 --> 1:19:36.189
♪ Please don’t stop ♪

1:19:38.441 --> 1:19:42.987
♪ Whatever you do ♪

1:19:43.070 --> 1:19:46.115
♪ See me through... ♪

1:19:46.199 --> 1:19:47.575
Hello there, gorgeous.

1:19:50.369 --> 1:19:51.704
Want?

1:19:51.787 --> 1:19:53.039
♪ Don’t stop loving me ♪

1:19:53.122 --> 1:19:54.499
♪ Don’t stop, don’t stop ♪

1:19:54.582 --> 1:19:55.583
No.

1:19:55.666 --> 1:19:57.001
♪ Don’t stop loving me ♪

1:19:57.084 --> 1:19:58.419
♪ Don’t stop, don’t stop ♪

1:19:58.503 --> 1:20:00.421
Thank you.

1:20:01.464 --> 1:20:03.090
♪ At last ♪

1:20:04.509 --> 1:20:07.136
♪ Make each moment last ♪

1:20:08.513 --> 1:20:13.142
♪ An eternity ♪

1:20:13.226 --> 1:20:16.312
♪ We just had to be... ♪

1:20:16.395 --> 1:20:19.023
(music continues faintly
in distance)

1:20:30.785 --> 1:20:33.120
("Give Me One More Chance"
by The Procedures playing)

1:20:33.204 --> 1:20:35.164
-♪ I know I caused our breakup ♪
-(quiet chatter)

1:20:35.248 --> 1:20:36.582
♪ Hurt you and made you cry... ♪

1:20:36.666 --> 1:20:39.126
TERI (quietly): See that guy
over there? That’s Mike.

1:20:39.210 --> 1:20:41.170
Stay here, okay?

1:20:41.254 --> 1:20:43.005
And keep to yourself.

1:20:43.089 --> 1:20:45.091
(music continues quietly)

1:20:53.224 --> 1:20:55.142
If it isn’t Old Firecracker.

1:20:55.226 --> 1:20:57.186
-Don’t call me old, asshole.
-(laughs)

1:20:57.270 --> 1:20:58.980
Come here.
(grunts softly)

1:20:59.063 --> 1:21:00.439
How are you?

1:21:02.316 --> 1:21:04.443
Never thought I’d see her again.

1:21:06.070 --> 1:21:07.697
How do you know her?

1:21:07.780 --> 1:21:10.199
She used to be married
to a guy I know.

1:21:12.201 --> 1:21:14.120
Eddie?

1:21:14.203 --> 1:21:15.705
You know Eddie?

1:21:17.707 --> 1:21:19.667
She just told me about him.

1:21:19.750 --> 1:21:23.170
Man, that was some shit.

1:21:25.006 --> 1:21:26.132
JEAN:
What?

1:21:26.215 --> 1:21:29.135
Oh, you don’t know?

1:21:29.218 --> 1:21:31.220
Watch yourself with her.

1:21:34.223 --> 1:21:36.267
She took everything from him.

1:21:36.350 --> 1:21:38.644
And I mean everything.

1:21:38.728 --> 1:21:43.149
But he started a whole new life
and a new family.

1:21:44.233 --> 1:21:47.153
Kept it far away
from this shithole.

1:21:47.236 --> 1:21:50.531
It’s like I said, just never
thought I’d see her again.

1:21:50.615 --> 1:21:52.366
TERI: Something’s going down.
We need to leave.

1:21:52.450 --> 1:21:54.452
Paul is Eddie’s son.

1:21:57.371 --> 1:21:58.998
Not now, Jean.

1:22:01.626 --> 1:22:04.378
Why didn’t you tell me?

1:22:04.462 --> 1:22:06.213
Eddie would keep me in the dark.

1:22:06.297 --> 1:22:08.633
Told me it was to protect me,
just like you, just like Cal,

1:22:08.716 --> 1:22:10.426
but I don’t believe it anymore.

1:22:10.509 --> 1:22:13.304
Is any of this real, or are you
just like the rest of them?

1:22:13.387 --> 1:22:14.513
(gunshot)

1:22:14.597 --> 1:22:16.599
-(people screaming)
-(gunfire)

1:22:19.935 --> 1:22:21.270
Shit, it’s locked.

1:22:21.354 --> 1:22:23.481
-Mike!
-(gunfire, screaming continue)

1:22:23.564 --> 1:22:25.399
Come on. Come on.

1:22:25.483 --> 1:22:27.485
(disco music playing loudly)

1:22:31.447 --> 1:22:32.448
What are you doing?

1:22:32.531 --> 1:22:33.991
Stay here.

1:22:34.075 --> 1:22:36.077
(screaming continues)

1:22:38.079 --> 1:22:40.831
(footsteps running past)

1:22:40.915 --> 1:22:43.250
-(gunfire continues)
-(people shouting)

1:22:43.334 --> 1:22:45.252
(banging on door)

1:22:45.336 --> 1:22:47.755
-(Jean panting)
-(gun cocks)

1:22:50.925 --> 1:22:52.635
(gunfire)

1:22:52.718 --> 1:22:54.720
(people screaming)

1:22:59.767 --> 1:23:01.769
-(gunfire stops)
-(Jean panting)

1:23:04.772 --> 1:23:06.691
(screaming and shouting fade)

1:23:06.774 --> 1:23:08.776
(disco music continues faintly
in distance)

1:23:23.541 --> 1:23:24.875
(men shouting)

1:23:24.959 --> 1:23:26.836
-(gunfire)
-(woman screams)

1:23:27.837 --> 1:23:29.004
(gunfire)

1:23:30.631 --> 1:23:32.341
-(people screaming)
-(disco music playing loudly)

1:23:32.425 --> 1:23:34.343
(Jean grunting)

1:23:34.427 --> 1:23:36.429
-(clamoring)
-(glass shattering)

1:23:49.734 --> 1:23:51.736
(clamoring continues
in distance)

1:23:54.530 --> 1:23:56.907
(panting)

1:23:56.991 --> 1:23:58.325
(door closes)

1:23:58.409 --> 1:24:00.411
(sirens wailing)

1:24:05.207 --> 1:24:07.209
(crowd clamoring)

1:24:14.091 --> 1:24:16.093
(horns honking)

1:24:21.599 --> 1:24:23.601
(panting)

1:24:34.236 --> 1:24:36.238
♪ ♪

1:24:51.045 --> 1:24:52.671
(siren wailing in distance)

1:24:54.673 --> 1:24:57.009
(people chattering and laughing
in distance)

1:24:57.092 --> 1:24:58.511
(sniffles)

1:25:10.856 --> 1:25:12.858
♪ ♪

1:25:20.658 --> 1:25:22.660
(thunder rumbling)

1:25:39.301 --> 1:25:41.303
(quiet chatter)

1:25:43.097 --> 1:25:45.099
(panting)

1:26:08.163 --> 1:26:10.165
You all right?

1:26:13.419 --> 1:26:15.421
(laughing softly)

1:26:19.091 --> 1:26:21.093
(woman humming quietly)

1:26:25.306 --> 1:26:27.308
(sobbing)

1:26:46.869 --> 1:26:48.495
It’s okay.

1:26:49.914 --> 1:26:51.999
(sobbing loudly)

1:26:52.082 --> 1:26:53.709
You’re okay.

1:26:58.297 --> 1:27:00.215
It’s okay.

1:27:00.299 --> 1:27:01.926
You’re okay.

1:27:06.138 --> 1:27:08.140
-(sobbing softly)
-(quietly): You’re okay.

1:27:09.475 --> 1:27:11.101
You’re okay.

1:27:11.185 --> 1:27:13.103
(sniffles) Thank you.

1:27:32.331 --> 1:27:34.333
(TV playing quietly)

1:27:39.380 --> 1:27:41.048
Room 12.

1:27:42.216 --> 1:27:44.259
(TV continues playing)

1:27:44.343 --> 1:27:46.595
(laughter nearby)

1:28:19.670 --> 1:28:21.672
(door opens)

1:28:23.173 --> 1:28:25.426
TERI:
I came back for you.

1:28:25.509 --> 1:28:27.511
But you were gone.

1:28:29.346 --> 1:28:30.597
Hi.

1:28:31.849 --> 1:28:35.811
Eddie and I had Paul
the year we got married.

1:28:35.894 --> 1:28:38.731
Soon after that, I found out
what he really did.

1:28:40.733 --> 1:28:42.526
I wanted to leave,

1:28:42.609 --> 1:28:47.031
but Eddie promised me that
his next job would be his last.

1:28:48.240 --> 1:28:50.868
It wasn’t. And it never was.

1:28:52.911 --> 1:28:54.830
Cal was Eddie’s guy.

1:28:54.913 --> 1:28:58.292
But he didn’t want it,
not the way Eddie did.

1:28:58.375 --> 1:29:00.377
I think it even
scared him a little.

1:29:02.588 --> 1:29:04.590
But he was always there.

1:29:04.673 --> 1:29:07.885
Always... even.

1:29:10.095 --> 1:29:11.889
We started
confiding in each other,

1:29:11.972 --> 1:29:16.602
and eventually we fell in love.

1:29:19.980 --> 1:29:22.941
It was Eddie
you were hiding from.

1:29:23.025 --> 1:29:24.610
When you were here.

1:29:28.447 --> 1:29:30.449
We came without a plan.

1:29:32.409 --> 1:29:35.329
We got restless, and we left.

1:29:35.412 --> 1:29:38.332
That’s when Eddie found us.

1:29:38.415 --> 1:29:41.418
He loved us too much to hurt us,
but he wasn’t gonna let us go

1:29:41.502 --> 1:29:44.254
without getting
something in return.

1:29:44.338 --> 1:29:47.299
So we made a deal.

1:29:47.382 --> 1:29:50.469
We would get to be together.

1:29:50.552 --> 1:29:52.763
We could get out.

1:29:55.140 --> 1:29:58.310
But one day Eddie would call,

1:29:58.393 --> 1:30:01.647
and Cal wouldn’t be able
to say no.

1:30:04.650 --> 1:30:06.276
That was me.

1:30:08.278 --> 1:30:09.905
That was you.

1:30:16.662 --> 1:30:20.999
I work at the university,
and Cal’s at a moving company.

1:30:22.459 --> 1:30:24.711
Paul thinks he’s his dad.

1:30:24.795 --> 1:30:27.798
-(pouring coffee)
-And a really good one.

1:30:34.930 --> 1:30:37.891
As time went on, we thought
it might really be over.

1:30:37.975 --> 1:30:42.104
That we might really have...
gotten out.

1:30:43.188 --> 1:30:44.815
We put the past in a box,

1:30:44.898 --> 1:30:48.694
and we put that box
in a secret drawer.

1:30:50.320 --> 1:30:52.865
And we thought
that maybe it would just...

1:30:54.908 --> 1:30:56.326
...disappear.

1:31:00.455 --> 1:31:02.207
I’m so sorry.

1:31:05.002 --> 1:31:06.420
(sighs softly)

1:31:10.007 --> 1:31:11.550
That guy Mike at the club--

1:31:11.633 --> 1:31:14.094
he’s a real piece of shit,
always has been.

1:31:14.178 --> 1:31:16.096
And I knew it would be
dangerous there.

1:31:16.180 --> 1:31:19.433
Things have been like that
since Eddie killed Marvin.

1:31:19.516 --> 1:31:22.853
But going there was
the best option we had.

1:31:22.936 --> 1:31:25.189
What do you mean?

1:31:25.272 --> 1:31:28.609
If I’m right, word will
get to Cal that I’m in the city,

1:31:28.692 --> 1:31:31.445
and once Cal knows that,
he’ll find us.

1:31:36.450 --> 1:31:38.619
Mike works with Eddie?

1:31:38.702 --> 1:31:41.246
They did some jobs together.

1:31:41.330 --> 1:31:43.332
Then Eddie shot his ear off.

1:31:51.548 --> 1:31:53.967
Mike called you "Firecracker."

1:31:56.887 --> 1:31:58.013
Was that...?

1:31:58.096 --> 1:32:00.432
Don’t tell me...

1:32:13.487 --> 1:32:15.572
So, what do we do now?

1:32:15.656 --> 1:32:18.033
We wait.

1:32:27.668 --> 1:32:29.670
♪ ♪

1:32:51.066 --> 1:32:53.068
♪ ♪

1:33:14.589 --> 1:33:16.591
(phone ringing)

1:33:21.013 --> 1:33:23.015
(ringing continues)

1:33:28.186 --> 1:33:29.354
Hello?

1:33:29.438 --> 1:33:30.814
Thank you.

1:33:32.441 --> 1:33:35.986
Teri, there’s some men
out front.

1:33:36.069 --> 1:33:38.071
We can go out the back.

1:33:42.909 --> 1:33:44.911
♪ ♪

1:33:47.914 --> 1:33:49.333
Thank you.

1:33:50.542 --> 1:33:52.544
I’ll meet you there.

1:34:00.344 --> 1:34:03.472
Jean, no matter what you hear,

1:34:03.555 --> 1:34:05.182
keep walking.

1:34:14.775 --> 1:34:16.109
(men talking in distance)

1:34:16.193 --> 1:34:17.736
MAN:
Hey, Teri.

1:34:17.819 --> 1:34:19.529
Came to talk to you, huh?

1:34:19.613 --> 1:34:20.822
Teri, where you going?

1:34:20.906 --> 1:34:22.783
(two gunshots)

1:34:22.866 --> 1:34:24.618
-(vehicle door closes)
-(engine starts)

1:34:24.701 --> 1:34:26.244
(tires screeching)

1:34:26.328 --> 1:34:28.330
("Even the Bluebirds Are Blue"
by Johnny Halo playing)

1:34:28.413 --> 1:34:30.791
♪ Even ♪

1:34:30.874 --> 1:34:33.251
♪ The bluebirds ♪

1:34:33.335 --> 1:34:37.339
♪ Are blue... ♪

1:34:42.511 --> 1:34:45.180
Where’s Teri?

1:34:45.263 --> 1:34:47.015
She said she’ll meet us here.

1:34:48.100 --> 1:34:49.226
Paul and Harry?

1:34:49.309 --> 1:34:51.853
With your dad at the cabin.

1:34:51.937 --> 1:34:54.398
(entry bell jingles)

1:34:54.481 --> 1:34:56.691
So, can I get you anything?

1:34:58.360 --> 1:34:59.653
Coffee.

1:34:59.736 --> 1:35:01.154
Two.

1:35:07.411 --> 1:35:09.579
Are you okay?

1:35:09.663 --> 1:35:11.415
Eddie’s dead.

1:35:11.498 --> 1:35:12.999
Here you go.

1:35:16.253 --> 1:35:18.255
At least it stopped
raining, right?

1:35:20.757 --> 1:35:22.050
Anything else?

1:35:22.134 --> 1:35:23.969
CAL:
No, thank you.

1:35:43.530 --> 1:35:45.866
I’ll get a job.

1:35:45.949 --> 1:35:47.367
What?

1:35:49.035 --> 1:35:51.037
An apartment, maybe.

1:35:53.039 --> 1:35:55.041
Someplace far away.

1:35:57.252 --> 1:35:59.254
Harry can grow up there.

1:36:03.300 --> 1:36:06.219
He won’t remember any of this.

1:36:06.303 --> 1:36:08.930
I know everything, Cal.

1:36:15.103 --> 1:36:17.272
(coughing softly)

1:36:23.153 --> 1:36:25.447
Do you need help?

1:36:25.530 --> 1:36:27.157
(inhales sharply)

1:36:28.492 --> 1:36:29.826
I’m all right.

1:36:29.910 --> 1:36:31.495
(entry bell jingles)

1:36:31.578 --> 1:36:34.414
("Call Me and I’ll Be Happy" by
The Teardrops playing quietly)

1:36:36.416 --> 1:36:38.001
Where is she?

1:36:40.128 --> 1:36:42.506
She’ll be here.

1:36:46.551 --> 1:36:48.553
Did Eddie do that?

1:36:51.640 --> 1:36:53.975
He was dead before I got there.

1:37:03.276 --> 1:37:04.903
(entry bell jingles)

1:37:31.304 --> 1:37:33.306
♪ ♪

1:37:52.117 --> 1:37:54.119
♪ ♪

1:38:03.920 --> 1:38:05.922
(lock clicking)

1:38:09.426 --> 1:38:10.844
(car door closes)

1:38:12.721 --> 1:38:14.931
CAL:
Take the Wilson Street Bridge.

1:38:15.015 --> 1:38:16.182
TERI:
But it’ll take longer.

1:38:16.266 --> 1:38:17.517
CAL:
Just stay off Central.

1:38:17.601 --> 1:38:18.935
TERI:
Why? We ditched the truck.

1:38:19.019 --> 1:38:21.646
-Teri.
-We have to get back
to the kids.

1:38:21.730 --> 1:38:22.856
CAL:
You’re the one who said

1:38:22.939 --> 1:38:23.982
Mike’s guys were
outside the hotel.

1:38:24.065 --> 1:38:25.191
I-I don’t trust them.

1:38:25.275 --> 1:38:27.110
TERI: Can’t believe
that asshole’s still alive.

1:38:27.193 --> 1:38:28.570
But Eddie’s dead.

1:38:29.779 --> 1:38:31.781
I don’t think he knows.

1:38:31.865 --> 1:38:33.867
(tires screeching in distance)

1:38:35.869 --> 1:38:37.370
Someone’s following us.

1:38:38.997 --> 1:38:40.206
-(bumpers thump)
-(grunts)

1:38:42.709 --> 1:38:44.127
(tires screeching)

1:38:46.171 --> 1:38:47.255
(horn blaring)

1:38:47.339 --> 1:38:48.673
(panting)

1:38:48.757 --> 1:38:50.300
(gasps)

1:38:56.848 --> 1:38:58.767
(horns honking)

1:39:03.855 --> 1:39:05.857
(horns honking)

1:39:19.913 --> 1:39:21.665
(horn blaring)

1:39:26.461 --> 1:39:27.671
(horn blaring)

1:39:39.349 --> 1:39:40.475
-(tires screeching)
-Whoa.

1:39:42.435 --> 1:39:43.645
(horn blaring)

1:39:43.728 --> 1:39:46.147
-(grunts)
-(panting)

1:39:46.231 --> 1:39:48.191
He’s gone. He’s gone.

1:40:01.496 --> 1:40:03.498
♪ ♪

1:40:25.562 --> 1:40:27.105
-(tires screeching)
-(grunting)

1:40:32.402 --> 1:40:34.738
(train horn blowing in distance)

1:40:39.367 --> 1:40:41.369
(steam hissing)

1:40:58.011 --> 1:40:59.429
(grunts softly)

1:41:11.441 --> 1:41:12.984
Cal.

1:41:13.067 --> 1:41:15.528
(vehicle approaching)

1:41:15.612 --> 1:41:17.614
-(brakes squeak)
-Teri.

1:41:19.616 --> 1:41:21.159
(footsteps approaching)

1:41:21.242 --> 1:41:22.660
Teri.

1:41:23.995 --> 1:41:25.538
No, no. No, no, no, no.

1:41:25.622 --> 1:41:27.165
Teri. (grunting)

1:41:27.248 --> 1:41:29.250
Teri! Cal!

1:41:29.334 --> 1:41:31.711
No. No.

1:41:31.795 --> 1:41:33.213
Teri!

1:41:34.422 --> 1:41:36.424
(grunting)

1:41:38.635 --> 1:41:40.053
Cal!

1:41:43.223 --> 1:41:45.225
(whimpering)

1:41:52.232 --> 1:41:54.234
(panting)

1:41:56.528 --> 1:41:59.447
(car door opens, closes)

1:41:59.531 --> 1:42:00.657
Is this her?

1:42:00.740 --> 1:42:02.742
Shut the fuck up.

1:42:13.878 --> 1:42:15.213
What’s happening?

1:42:15.296 --> 1:42:17.131
Shut the fuck up!

1:42:18.675 --> 1:42:21.553
-This is Jean?
-Yes!

1:42:21.636 --> 1:42:22.762
Eddie’s wife?

1:42:22.846 --> 1:42:24.556
Jesus Christ!

1:42:24.639 --> 1:42:25.807
(tires screech)

1:42:26.975 --> 1:42:28.518
(gunshot)

1:42:28.601 --> 1:42:31.354
(Jean whimpering)

1:42:33.231 --> 1:42:36.192
Did I not tell this asshole
to shut the fuck up?

1:42:44.200 --> 1:42:46.619
It’s nice to finally
meet you, Jean.

1:42:49.122 --> 1:42:52.125
I’m sorry I didn’t know
that was you in my club.

1:42:53.710 --> 1:42:56.421
(panting)

1:43:05.680 --> 1:43:07.056
Where’s Eddie?

1:43:08.141 --> 1:43:09.809
Eddie’s dead.

1:43:10.852 --> 1:43:13.354
Jean, Jean, Jean.

1:43:13.438 --> 1:43:14.981
Don’t do that.

1:43:17.400 --> 1:43:18.693
Don’t lie to me.

1:43:18.776 --> 1:43:21.821
Don’t you know
this is the moment

1:43:21.905 --> 1:43:24.324
this can all be over?

1:43:24.407 --> 1:43:25.825
All’s you have to...

1:43:25.909 --> 1:43:28.077
(gunshot)

1:43:30.330 --> 1:43:33.333
(body slumps over)

1:43:52.810 --> 1:43:54.812
(panting)

1:43:57.523 --> 1:43:59.525
(grunting)

1:44:27.512 --> 1:44:29.514
(tires screeching)

1:44:41.943 --> 1:44:43.361
(tires screech)

1:44:52.286 --> 1:44:53.705
Teri?

1:44:55.164 --> 1:44:56.791
(panting)

1:45:01.671 --> 1:45:02.880
(whispering):
Teri.

1:45:03.923 --> 1:45:05.341
Teri.

1:45:07.719 --> 1:45:10.096
Okay. Okay.

1:45:16.561 --> 1:45:18.563
(grunting)

1:45:28.865 --> 1:45:30.199
(grunts loudly)

1:45:30.283 --> 1:45:31.909
(panting)

1:45:33.286 --> 1:45:35.163
(grunting loudly)

1:45:41.252 --> 1:45:43.254
(grunting loudly)

1:45:48.259 --> 1:45:50.261
(panting)

1:45:52.722 --> 1:45:54.098
(grunts)

1:45:54.182 --> 1:45:56.184
(panting)

1:46:10.406 --> 1:46:12.408
(grunting)

1:46:14.494 --> 1:46:16.496
(train horn blowing in distance)

1:46:22.627 --> 1:46:25.213
I’m okay. I’m okay.

1:46:32.011 --> 1:46:33.930
(grunts)

1:46:34.013 --> 1:46:35.932
(door creaking)

1:46:36.015 --> 1:46:38.017
(panting)

1:46:42.563 --> 1:46:44.565
(Cal breathes deeply)

1:46:46.567 --> 1:46:47.985
(softly):
Okay.

1:46:51.197 --> 1:46:53.199
(grunting)

1:46:54.575 --> 1:46:56.577
(grunting loudly)

1:46:58.579 --> 1:47:00.581
(panting)

1:47:20.726 --> 1:47:22.728
(both grunting)

1:47:35.199 --> 1:47:37.201
(both grunting)

1:47:52.466 --> 1:47:54.468
(panting)

1:48:02.602 --> 1:48:04.020
Go.

1:48:06.480 --> 1:48:08.107
I killed Mike.

1:48:09.650 --> 1:48:10.985
(engine revs)

1:48:11.068 --> 1:48:13.070
♪ ♪

1:48:32.048 --> 1:48:34.050
♪ ♪

1:48:56.781 --> 1:48:59.242
(panting)

1:49:16.634 --> 1:49:18.052
TERI:
Jean.

1:49:19.053 --> 1:49:21.097
I don’t think I can move.

1:49:23.224 --> 1:49:25.643
(voice shaking):
I don’t think I can move.

1:49:34.235 --> 1:49:36.153
(engine idling)

1:49:36.237 --> 1:49:38.239
♪ ♪

1:49:58.259 --> 1:50:00.261
♪ ♪

1:50:12.565 --> 1:50:14.567
♪ ♪

1:50:37.006 --> 1:50:39.008
♪ ♪

1:50:45.139 --> 1:50:46.557
